I'm deciding which one to use. I'm going to write another book.
不是，我想选一本来用 我又要写书了

25
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:07,250
Because the last one was such a big seller?
因为上一本很畅销？

26
00:02:07,890 --> 00:02:10,720
If you must know, I have written 14 books.
告诉你，我已经写了十四本书

27
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,730
And as I'm the only one who has read them...
因为读者只有我一个

28
00:02:13,930 --> 00:02:17,390
I can tell you that they have been well received.
我可以告诉你们，反应很热烈

29
00:02:19,670 --> 00:02:21,500
But I lost all of them in the fire.
但是火灾把那些书都烧了

30
00:02:21,670 --> 00:02:26,370
So this one I'm gonna keep in an asbestos-lined box far away from Rachel.
所以这本我要收在防火箱里 放得离瑞秋远远的

31
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:29,780
Who I forgive.
我原谅她

32
00:02:33,050 --> 00:02:34,410
What are you doing later?
你们等一下有事吗？

33
00:02:34,620 --> 00:02:36,880
Rachel and I have to get our hair cut.
瑞秋和我要去剪头发

34
00:02:37,650 --> 00:02:39,240
-We do? -I wanna see what he wants.
-有吗？ -我想先知道他要干嘛

35
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:44,120
Elizabeth's dad wants to meet me.
我刚得知伊丽莎白她爸想见我

36
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:46,420
Wait a minute. Hold the phone.
等等，且慢

37
00:02:46,590 --> 00:02:48,720
You're not Elizabeth's dad?
你不是伊丽莎白的爸爸？

38
00:02:52,470 --> 00:02:54,660
That's the only one you get.
你只能亏我这一次

39
00:02:55,470 --> 00:02:56,560
And he hates me.
他讨厌我

40
00:02:56,740 --> 00:02:59,610
He asked Elizabeth why she'd want to go out with a guy...
他问伊丽莎白为何要跟一个 

41
00:02:59,770 --> 00:03:01,770
who couldn't get a girl his own age.
不交同年龄女友的男人约会

42
00:03:02,740 --> 00:03:05,270
And what did she say to that?
那她怎么说？

43
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:08,550
And that's yours.
你也不能再亏我了

44
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,580
Come on. I really want this guy to like me.
拜托啦，我真的想让他喜欢我 

45
00:03:11,790 --> 00:03:15,810
It would really help if you guys could make me look good.
你们要是能捧我一下就太好了

46
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:18,050
-Of course we'll help. -Thanks.
-我们当然会帮忙的啦。 -谢谢。

47
00:03:18,630 --> 00:03:22,790
We know how tough those parent-teacher conferences can be.
谁都知道参加母姐会很辛苦

48
00:03:26,830 --> 00:03:30,100
-So here's your office set. -Wow!
这是你的办公室场景

49
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:35,540
Mac Machiavelli,private investigator.
麦克麦可维利，私家侦探

50
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:40,770
Look at all the books I've read.
你看我读这么多书

51
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,140
Let's get you to wardrobe.
我带你去试戏服 好

52
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:46,410
When do I meet the robot?
什么时候跟机器人见面？

53
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:49,350
Right now. He's right here.
抱歉，那就现在吧，他也在

54
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,360
Joey Tribbiani,this is..
乔伊崔比亚尼，这位…

55
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:54,490
Wow! He's so lifelike.
真是栩栩如生

56
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:56,890
Unbelievable.
了不起 

57
00:03:57,100 --> 00:04:00,530
This is Wayne,the man who created and operates C.H.E.E.S.E.
这位是创造、操作吉事的韦恩

58
00:04:00,770 --> 00:04:02,530
How do you do there,buddy?
韦恩，你好

59
00:04:03,270 --> 00:04:05,760
I'll let you two guys get acquainted.
你们两个慢慢聊 好

60
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:07,270
Sorry about that.
刚才很抱歉

61
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:11,640
-So where's C.H.E.E.S.E.? -C.H.E.E.S.E. is right here.
-吉事呢？ -吉事就在这里

62
00:04:17,550 --> 00:04:19,380
Nice to meet you,Mac.
麦克，幸会

63
00:04:22,890 --> 00:04:26,550
-This is the temporary robot,right? -No. Why?
-它是半成品吧？ -不是，怎么了？

64
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:30,290
I thought it was gonna be a really cool robot.
我以为它会长得很酷

66
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:33,760
Like the Terminator, or when I first saw you.
像魔鬼终结者，或刚才的你

67
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:38,460
I spent two years developing this. It's state of the art.
我花了2年研发这台机器 它非常先进

68
00:04:38,670 --> 00:04:41,640
Sorry. It doesn't look like it can do anything.
抱歉，只是它看起来一无是处

69
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:43,340
It can do this.
它会这样

70
00:04:55,820 --> 00:04:59,690
This is my father, Paul Stevens. Dad, this is Ross Geller.
这是我爸，保罗史提芬斯 爸，这是罗斯盖勒

71
00:04:59,990 --> 00:05:02,020
It's great to meet you,Paul.
保罗，你好

72
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:05,830
I prefer that Liz's boyfriends address me as Mr. Stevens.
我比较喜欢伊丽莎白的男友 叫我史提芬斯先生

73
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:09,530
Of course. Mr. Stevens.
没问题，史提芬斯先生

74
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,330
So,Ross...
罗斯…

75
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:14,360
what's your problem?
你有什么毛病？

76
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:17,470
Excuse me?
什么？ 

77
00:05:17,810 --> 00:05:19,870
Why can't you get a girlfriend your own age?
为什么不交年龄相近的女友？

78
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:23,280
It's funny...
真好笑…

79
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:25,550
It's not funny.
不好笑

80
00:05:26,220 --> 00:05:28,810
I don't like you going out with my daughter,Ross.
我不喜欢你跟我女儿交往

81
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:31,960
Okay,I can see that.
好，我看得出来

82
00:05:32,290 --> 00:05:36,730
I think if you give me one chance, I can change your mind.
但要是你给我机会 我一定能改变你的看法

83
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:39,330
-Okay. -What?
-好。 -什么？

84
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,860
Okay. I'll give you one chance to change my mind.
好，我给你机会改变我的看法

85
00:05:43,670 --> 00:05:46,270
You've got one minute.
计时1分钟

86
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:50,970
-Daddy. -Fine. Two minutes. Go.
-爸 -好吧 2分钟，开始

88
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:58,410
A minute and 50 seconds.
1分50秒

89
00:05:59,090 --> 00:06:02,820
I want you to know, I've never done anything like this before.
好，我以前没做过这种事

90
00:06:03,090 --> 00:06:06,190
I mean,I've been in relationships in general.
我是说我跟别人交往过

91
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:09,560
But I've never done it with a student. I mean,not...
但是我没跟学生做过…不…

92
00:06:11,470 --> 00:06:14,160
Not "it." We haven't done "it."
不是那档事，我们还没做过

93
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,900
I mean,we've done stuff...
当然我们做过一些事…

94
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:24,240
Okay. A joke. Lighten the mood.
好，讲个笑话轻松一下

95
00:06:24,510 --> 00:06:27,000
Two guys go into a bar. One of them is Irish.
两个男人走进酒吧 一个是爱尔兰人

96
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:31,310
-I'm Irish. -And the Irish guy wins the joke.
-我是爱尔兰人 -结果爱尔兰人赢了

97
00:06:33,050 --> 00:06:36,020
Ross! How crazy that we would run into you.
罗斯，居然会在这里遇见你

98
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:38,220
Oh,my God! Thank you.
天哪，谢谢你们

99
00:06:40,030 --> 00:06:44,290
I'd like you to meet my friends. This is Phoebe, Monica and Chandler.
史提芬斯先生，他们是我朋友 菲比，摩妮卡和钱德

100
00:06:44,830 --> 00:06:45,890
-Phoebe. -Hello.
菲比

101
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,300
-Monica. -Hi.
摩妮卡

102
00:06:47,470 --> 00:06:48,990
Chunder.
强德

103
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:51,160
-Chandler. -Never going to remember that.
是钱德 我记不住的

104
00:06:53,610 --> 00:06:56,840
You're Elizabeth's dad? I see where she gets her...
你是伊丽莎白的父亲？ 难怪她有一种…

105
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,770
rugged handsomeness.
粗犷的美

106
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:03,980
Is there a Mrs. Stevens?
你有老婆吗？

107
00:07:05,690 --> 00:07:07,180
There's a Mr. Bing!
你有老公

108
00:07:09,490 --> 00:07:13,190
Unfortunately,Lizzie's mom passed away after she was born.
没有，丽莎出生不久 她妈妈就过世了

109
00:07:14,030 --> 00:07:16,090
I raised her by myself.
我一手把她带大

110
00:07:17,030 --> 00:07:18,460
I get that a lot.
我常碰上这种反应

111
00:07:20,470 --> 00:07:23,100
Why don't we all take a seat?
好，大家都坐吧

112
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:26,670
I'll get us all some coffees.
我去帮大家点个咖啡

113
00:07:26,970 --> 00:07:28,500
Yeah,why don't you...
你来

114
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:32,280
Talk about whatever you want.
你们先随便聊 

115
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:35,310
Whatever pops into your head.
想到什么就聊什么

116
00:07:37,190 --> 00:07:39,950
It is strange seeing Ross here, this time of day...
这时候在这里遇见罗斯真怪 

117
00:07:40,150 --> 00:07:42,880
because usually he's at the children's hospital.
他通常都要去儿童医院

118
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:46,120
But not looking for dates.
不是去泡美眉喔

119
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,520
Monica is Ross's sister.
摩妮卡是罗斯的妹妹

120
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,460
He's a great brother!
他是个很棒的哥哥 

121
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:56,530
I had a sister.
我也有一个妹妹

122
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,270
She passed away.
她过世了

123
00:07:58,610 --> 00:08:01,040
You don't have to do that every time.
你们不必每次都这样

124
00:08:01,410 --> 00:08:05,540
But Ross is a great guy. I was roommates with him in college.
不过罗斯人真的很好 我们是大学室友

125
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,040
Funny story...
好笑的是…

126
00:08:08,550 --> 00:08:11,380
Your roommate in college died, didn't he?
你的大学室友死了对吧？

127
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,850
A part of him did,yes.
他算是半死不活

128
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:18,250
Here we are,Paul,Elizabeth.
来吧，保罗，伊丽莎白 

129
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:21,090
I hope you guys are finding something to talk about.
希望你们有找到话题

130
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:23,230
-Yes. We were just.. -Sorry I'm late.
-我们正在… -抱歉我来晚了

131
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,590
But I am ready to talk you up.
不过我已经准备好要捧你了

132
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:30,030
-When does Liz's father get here? -I'm already here.
-丽莎的爸爸什么时候来？ -我已经来了

133
00:08:30,470 --> 00:08:33,440
Ross is so great!
罗斯人最好了

134
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:40,310
Hey,Phoebe. How's the book writing going?
菲比，书写得怎样？

135
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:43,040
Really well. I'm up to page 47.
很好，我写到47页了

136
00:08:43,220 --> 00:08:45,280
-Wow! What are you writing? -Page numbers.
-你在写些什么？ -页数

137
00:08:46,950 --> 00:08:48,950
Honey,you got the kind with the little girl.
你买印小女生的 

138
00:08:49,490 --> 00:08:51,290
You said you'd buy the kind with the baby.
你明明说要买印小宝宝的

139
00:08:51,490 --> 00:08:54,550
-You said the baby creeps you out. -The little girl does.
-你说那个小宝宝有点恐怖 -是小女生有点恐怖

140
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:57,290
-You said the baby. -Why would a baby creep me out?
-你是说小宝宝 -小宝宝为什么会恐怖？ 

142
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:00,230
Why would the little girl creep you out?
小女生为什么会恐怖？

143
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:02,800
Can you please talk a little slower?
抱歉，你们讲慢一点好吗？ 

144
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,340
-This is for your book? -It's about relationships.
-你要写进书里？ 对，这是探讨男女关系的书 

145
00:09:05,540 --> 00:09:08,070
The traps,the pitfalls, what not to do.
尔虞我诈，各种禁忌

146
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:10,440
Keep going. This stuff's great.
继续，太精彩了

147
00:09:11,150 --> 00:09:12,810
Excuse me.
你说什么？

148
00:09:12,980 --> 00:09:17,420
And how none of it matters when the people really love each other.
还有真心相爱就能克服一切

149
00:09:18,550 --> 00:09:22,990
And how people will believe anything as long as it's a compliment.
还有人都喜欢听好话

150
00:09:29,430 --> 00:09:31,060
-Oh,hi! -Hi.

151
00:09:32,130 --> 00:09:36,130
-I left my keys here somewhere. -Well,let's look for them.
-我把钥匙掉在这里 -那赶快找

153
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:39,140
Hey,look! Are these them?
是这一串吗？

154
00:09:41,410 --> 00:09:43,240
No.
不是

155
00:09:43,910 --> 00:09:45,210
All right.
好吧

156
00:09:47,350 --> 00:09:48,870
-Here they are. -Good.
在这里 太好了 

157
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,910
-Thanks for your help. -Wait! Sorry!
谢谢你 等等

158
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,020
-Mr. Paul? -Just call me Paul.
保罗先生 叫我保罗就好 

159
00:09:53,220 --> 00:09:56,190
Paul. I just wanted you to know that...
保罗 我只是想说...

160
00:09:56,390 --> 00:09:58,590
Ross really is a great guy.
罗斯人真的很好

161
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:02,990
Maybe you could date him. It'd save me the trouble of killing him.
不如你跟他交往 省得我宰了他

162
00:10:07,470 --> 00:10:08,460
Are you okay?
怎么了？ 

163
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:11,670
You don't look old enough to have a 20-year-old daughter.
你不像是有20岁女儿的人

164
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:14,270
Well,we were very young when we had her.
我们生她的时候很年轻 

165
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:17,930
-We? -It usually takes two people to...
我们？ 对，一男一女才能…

167
00:10:18,650 --> 00:10:21,010
Oh,no! Yes! Of course. I know that!
当然，我知道

168
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:26,020
What I meant was are you still "we" or are you just you?
现在也是我们 还是只剩下你？

169
00:10:26,290 --> 00:10:27,480
I'm just me.
只有我

170
00:10:28,290 --> 00:10:30,950
My wife died shortly after Lizzie was born.
丽莎出生没多久 我老婆就死了

171
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:34,520
So you raised her all on your own?
你一手把她带大？ 

172
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,020
Yes,I did.
对

173
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:45,330
-What are you writing there? -I'm drawing a picture of you.
你在写什么？ 我在画你

174
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:47,700
Well,that's very flattering.
真好 

175
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:51,470
But it'd be great if you could draw me with some clothes and a head.
但要是有穿衣服有头会更好

176
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,510
How was your first day?
第一天顺利吗？

177
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:59,240
Pretty good. Except I got attitude from the robot.
不错，但机器人的态度有点差

178
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:03,180
Damn those robots. They're supposed to be our faithful servants!
